Maintainer: The package maintainer <alessandro.zito@duke.edu>
Description: BayesANT is a package for the taxonomic classification 
  of DNA sequences. It trains a taxonomic classifier on a dataset of DNA barcodes
  and returns probabilistic predictions for query DNA sequences. BayesANT
  explicitly accounts for potential taxonomic novelty of the query sequences by relying on 
  Bayesian nonparametric species sampling priors to model the taxonomic tree. 
